Scandit provides a sample code in C language to demonstrate how to load images from disk, initialize a barcode scanner, and handle recognized results.

WorldTidesLib Java Sample Code by FaMe IT contains a library to calculate tidal predictions and extremes (high and low tide) from the tidal constituents that can be retrieved from http://www.worldtides.info
Category: Nature, Data-as-a-Service, Geography, Marine, Predictions, Time, Water

Description: The Recorded Future Python Sample Code by Recorded Future shows features to look up for attackers, malware, and cyber attacks. Useful to prevent vulnerability when integrating the intelligence API into analytics applications.

The Recorded Future Java Sample Code by Recorded Future demonstrates how to work with the API, aiming to offer developers the tools to implement apps with intelligence features. Read only. Samples in JAR file available in Google Code. By author Evan Sparks.

The Imgur Objective-C Sample Code by Imgur demonstrates how to make API calls in iOS and OS X applications. ImgurSession works with OAuth 2.0 and also with anonymous sessions. Visual example available at http://imgur.com/gallery/63Gv6

The Imgur Android Sample Code by Imgur demonstrates how to use the API on Android. Calls are made using Retrofit, a REST client for Android and Java. Configuration available using Android studio. By Anthony Kiniyalocts.
This SMSAPI PHP Sample Code by SMSAPI explains how to send SMS messages, and how to send SMS messages by using the POST method.

With the CallRail PHP Sample Code by CallRail, developers can learn how to interact with the API by reading lines of code. Examples demonstrate how to replace with an Api Key, examine metadata from the response, and loop through companies. CallRail offers telephony as a main service, providing in addition messaging, transcription, and voice solutions to enterprises.

The CallRail Ruby Sample Code by CallRail demonstrates how to interact with the API telephony features. Examples show how to replace with an API Key, request a list of companies, parse the JSON response, examine metadata from the response, access the array of companies, and loop through companies.

The Google Classroom JavaScript Sample Code by Google helps developers to study the API interaction for educational integration projects. A quick start guide shows how to enable the Classroom API, set up the sample, and run the sample. Documentation is available for further development.

The Google Classroom iOS Sample Code by Google demonstrates how to interact with the API. This quick start guide explains how to enable the Classroom API, download the client library, prepare the project, set up the sample, and run the sample.

With the Google Classroom Android Sample Code by Google, developers can study how to work with the API features of accounts, collaboration, and domain for educational integration purposes in Java. References demonstrate how to acquire a SHA1 fingerprint, enable the classroom API, create a new Android project, configure the project, add source files, and run the app.

The Google Classroom .NET Sample Code by Google demonstrates how to interact with the API in a quick start guide. Contents explain how to enable the Classroom API, prepare the project, set up the sample, and run the sample. Documentation available for further development.

The Evernote Java Sample Code by Evernote shows how to make several API calls by using Java. Normally, Evernote requires the use of OAuth authorization, but a developer Token can be used as well. This Sample Code demonstrates a way by which developers can integrate the Evernote API into their applications.
Category: Personal Information Management, Classification, Mobile, Notes, Office

Description: The Glidera Java Sample Code by Glidera shows how to buy Bitcoin by using Java. This Sample Code demonstrates a way by which developers can integrate the Glidera API into their applications.

The WhatIsMyBrowser.com JavaScript Sample Code by WhatIsMyBrowser.com describes how to process a user agent string. This Sample Code specifies a way by which developers can integrate the WhatIsMyBrowser.com API into their applications.

The WhatIsMyBrowser.com PHP Sample Code by WhatIsMyBrowser.com describes how to process a user agent string. This Sample Code specifies a way by which developers can integrate the WhatIsMyBrowser.com API into their applications.

Skyttle Sentiment and Keywords Python Sample Code by Skyttle contains information about parameter request with three separate API calls, responses with annotated XML tags, and sentiment recognition with keyword extraction.

Skyttle Sentiment Analysis Python Sample Code by Skyttle presents how to analyze sentiment working with the API. Contains steps to detect positive and negative attitudes of any given text. Also provides Python parameters request and JSON response fields.

The Google DoubleClick Python Sample Code by Google is available on the Google Ads' GitHub site. In the same place developers can find examples that demonstrate DoubleClick interaction, they can also find a client library for AdWords, OAuth 2.0 integration, and both libraries for Advertisers API and Publishers API.

Google offers a sample code in PHP language to demonstrate the interaction with the DoubleClick API. This resource contains elements to study book-keeping, reports, and statements. What the API can do for developers is to integrate advertising campaigns features into mobile and web applications. Ads and AdWords are two additional APIs that could be of help when planning mobile monetization strategies.

The Google DoubleClick .NET Sample Code by Google demonstrates how to work with the API, with Ads, and with AdWords, three components that aim to facilitate the integration with DoubleClick's advertising features. To learn more, visit https://www.doubleclickbygoogle.com/solutions/revenue-management/dfp/

Google DoubleClick for publishers features a sample code in Java language to demonstrate the interaction with the API. Functionalities of the API are related to advertising campaigns across all screens. Capabilities of the API include an integrated sales management platform that aims to simplify selling and booking.

Better Doctor helps developers to find out how to integrate a list of insurance providers and plans, using a JavaScript Sample Code. With 3 main classifications: name, user identifier, and category, applications in websites and mobile phones could simplify healthcare search.

The Better Doctor List Conditions JavaScript sample code aims to facilitate the search of understanding and solutions according to patient's condition. The example displays results with overview, causes, symptoms, treatment, and prevention. Resources include national institutions such as Mayo Clinic, National Institute of Arthritis, and American Academy of Dermatology in the case of acne, the first case.

Better Doctor List Specialties JavaScript sample code provides code to integrate medical concentrations into websites and mobile applications. Besides the JavaScript sample, the specialties' results display unique identifier, name, category, description, actor, and actors. In the case of acupuncture, the uid would be acupuncturist, the name, acupuncture, the category, medical, the actor, acupuncturist, and the actors, acupuncturists. Includes short description of each specialty.

Better Doctor intends to facilitate physician search with the sample code in JavaScript language. Besides the code, the illustrated example shows name of doctor, star reviews, title, and picture. If the link is clicked, it automatically redirects to the doctor's page which includes contact info, insurance verification, map, biography, and Yelp reviews.

The Google Nearby Java sample code by Google demonstrates how to use the Nearby Connections API with the purpose to connect 2 devices and send messages. It contains steps to build and run the project. Additional resource includes a link to the API. Authored on GitHub by Sam Stern, Developer Programs Engineer at Google.

Yahoo offers the Python sample code to illustrate the interaction with the API web services. The file, that downloads automatically, offers Python class with test cases for Y! Mail and Y! Photos. With the goal to serve better the developer community, Yahoo! invites to migrate projects to IMAP. Get in touch at imap-service@yahoo-inc.com.

Yahoo! offers a PERL sample code to demonstrate the interaction with API web services. This file downloads automatically to a computer and the contents include Perl class with test cases for Y! Mail and Y! Photos. Beginning 2015, Yahoo! will migrate projects from the previous API to IMAP service, due to popularity among developers and change to OAuth2. Request more information at imap-service@yahoo-inc.com

The Yahoo! Mail Java sample code by Yahoo! downloads automatically from the official site. Although this example is valid to communicate with the API, Yahoo soon will migrate projects to IMAP to to a change of authentication from OAuth1 to OAuth2. For more information, send e-mail to imap-service@yahoo-inc.com

The Yahoo! Mail C# sample code by Yahoo! demonstrates how to communicate with web service. It requires
Yahoo! Mail WSDL. The Yahoo! Mail API uses OAuth as authentication method. Developers who have worked in the past with this API, can contact Yahoo! to migrate their projects to IMAP. Send e-mail to imap-service@yahoo-inc.com

The API.AI Unity sample code shows how to use the plugin with the goal to develop applications with natural language processing features. The API.AI uses voices commands and dialog scenarios. Such tools could simplify voice recognition and machine learning projects. For more information about the API, visit http://api.ai/
Category: Natural Language Processing, Machine Learning, Recognition

Description: The MailChimp Ruby sample code by Jesse demonstrates how to set up a development environment, interact with the API, and display results. It provides installation, with steps to either clone the repository or download the code example. It also offers to run dependencies, edit with the Api Key, and run with rails server.

The MailChimp Python sample code by Jesse displays how to interact with the API capabilities of e-mail marketing. With this tool, developers can study how to set up a wrapper, make API calls, and consume results in Python language. To interact with the sample, clone the repository and add the commands available on GitHub. Next, enter the Api Key and run the test.

Official Walk Score JavaScript Sample Code. It demonstrates how to interact with the AJAX API, providing an overview with resources to make a call on a server, call the Walk Score API, and understand the interaction written in JavaScript language. After revieweing this sample, developers have opportunities of API integration that include to add Walk Score into a site, add Walk Score into property listings, and enable searching by Walk Score.

The MailChimp PHP Sample Code by Josh Williams demonstrates how to set up the wrapper, make API calls, and consume results. Although developers can consult the API v2 documentation for testing purposes, this example should offer a framework to start. Installation guide included. Invitation open for developers who want to contribute.

The MailChimp Node.js sample code by Pete Holiday explains with an application the way to interact with the official wrapper. It allows developers to set up a common environment for integration, make API calls, and display the results. Node.js wrapper available at https://www.npmjs.com/package/mailchimp-api
This example provides source code for generating a server side address and process payment callback in Java programming language for the Blockchain Receive Payments API.
This sample provides source code for processing payments using Blockchain Receive Payments API and PHP programming language.

The PayPal Node.js Sample Code by PayPal demonstrate how to interact with the payments and invoicing features of the API. Examples include topics such as credit card, notifications, payments, sales, and subscriptions.

The PayPal Java Sample Code by PayPal demonstrates how to interact with the Adaptive Accounts, Adaptive Payments, Permissions, Invoicing, and Merchant APIs. Resources include SDK integration available at http://paypal.github.io/sdk/.
The Google Cast iOS Sample Code by Google provides guides to broadcast videos to a compatible big screen from an iOS mobile device. Includes dependencies, setup instructions, and documentation.

The Google Cast Android Sample Code by Google demonstrates how to interact with the Remote Display API, useful to broadcast to a compatible big screen from an Android mobile device. Includes references and setup instructions.

The Mendeley Ruby sample code by Mendeley, demonstrates how to perform a search for a catalog document using an identifier type, according to Mendeley Stack. Resources available on GitHub include sample code and the sample app that consumes the API.

The Mendeley R sample code by Mendeley shares code and its respective application that consumes the Mendeley API. This app retrieves the number of users that have read a document according to a DOI, producing a barplot of readers by academic status. To run the example, register client at http://dev.mendeley.com/ and follow 3 more steps available on GitHub. Authored by Matt Thomson.

This is a Mendeley Python sample code by Mendeley, authored by Matt Thomson on GitHub. It demonstrates how an application consumed the Mendeley API and how the sample code could be of help for developers. The application was built with Flask and Jinja2. It contains instructions to run the app from beginning to end.

The Mendeley JavaScript sample code by Mendeley supplements the SDK in the same language and the API available on the official site. What developers can find on GitHub, is an application that consumes the Mendeley API along with its respective code in JavaScript. Authored by Mendeley Stack.

The Google Translate Ruby sample code by Google contains demonstrations to improve understanding of the API functionalities of Google Translate, Google AdSense, Google Calendar, Google Drive, Google Plus, and Google Prediction. Created by nat@natwelch.com

In early stage, the Google Translate Node.js sample code displays a directory with variables and documents with analyticswrite, compute, customsearch, defaultauth, mediaupload, oauth2, and urlshortener. Created by Chris Bolin, software engineer at Jumpshell.

This Google Translate sample code by Google is available in early stage to demonstrate how to interact with the API in Go language. Additional to the Translate API, developers have access to examples for MapsEngine, Calendar, and Gmail APIs.

The page in which the Google Translate Python sample code is available, contains running samples to use a command-line or to script Google App Engine locally. For both options, common steps include to access the Google Developer Console, create a new project, enable APIs, select credentials, and create new ClientID.

This is a Google Translate sample code found on Google and available on GitHub. PHP language could assist users in the understanding of the API and the developing of translation projects. Project authored by woofyman99.

Google Translate JavaScript Sample Code by Google. This HTTPS resource in beta aims to demonstrate two main library functionalities: Loading an API and making a request & Authorizing and making authorized requests. Additional samples are available in the project source at https://github.com/google/google-api-javascript-client#hg%2Fsamples

The Instagram ActionScript sample code demonstrates how to interact with the API capabilities to share media and meet users. Author Khaled Garbaya created this project based on the Instagram ActionScript 3 library available at https://github.com/Khaledgarbaya/Instagras
For more information, contact khaledgarbaya@gmail.com

TripAdvisor tutorial slides that demonstrate how to integrate with the API. Created by Dick Brouwer, Director of Mobile Engineering at Trip Advisor. Video version is available at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bcfHyyeuVG8

ClickBank Python Sample Code by ClickBank. Displays how to interact with the API functionalities to request a refund for a customer's purchase, request a cancelation for a customer's subscription, and retrieve a list of transactions in a ClickBank account for a given time frame. The REST format supports Analytics, Images, Orders, Products, Shipping, Tickets, Sandbox, Ship Notice, Sandbox Product Creation, and Quickstats APIs.

ClickBank PHP Sample Code by ClickBank. Demonstrates how to interact with the capabilities of the API that include request refunds, request cancellations, and retrieve a list of transactions in a ClickBank account. Note that the API is for use for those developers in advanced stages, according to ClickBank.

The ClickBank Java Sample Code by ClickBank demonstrates how to access the API with Android implementation in mind. With this Java sample, developers can access a number of supported ClickBank APIs that include Analytics API, Images API, Orders API, Products API, Shipping API, Tickets API, Sandbox API, Ship Notice API, Sandbox Product Creation API, and Quickstats API.

ClickBank is a global internet provider to sell and promote digital products. The ClickBank C# Sample Code is available with the aim to simplify interaction with the API, which includes functionalities to request a refund for a customer's purchase, request a cancellation for a customer's subscription, and retrieve a list of transactions in a ClickBank account. For additional integration resources, visit https://support.clickbank.com/entries/22821303-ClickBank-API

NationBuilder aims to be the world's first operating system for community. With features of people, website, communications, and finances; users can build customized applications associated with change agents, social activism, and civil rights. The NationBuilder Python Sample Code offers to simplify the interaction with the API providing guides for installation, OAuth2 service, token, and API session. To know more about what developers can build with Python, visit http://nationbuilder.com/developers

NationBuilder is a software for social change. It can be used by a community, the government, or an independent organization. The NationBuilder Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to work with the OAuth2 Ruby gem to interact with NationBuilder. It contains instructions to build a client object, request an access token, consume resources, receive JSON responses, and refresh current token.

The official page of the NationBuilder Sample Codes demonstrates how to authenticate to a nation in PHP; add a person to a nation in PHP, Go, and Python; import pages from a CSV in Ruby; sync users between nation and a third party service in PHP; and manage events in a nation in C#. Includes endpoints, API explorer, and API developers forum with the aim to facilitate integration into websites and applications.

The Google Drive REST API JavaScript Sample Code by Google demonstrates how to open and save files with the Google Drive API in JavaScript. This project authored by Steve Bazyl was built by AngularJS and installed with Gulp and Bower. Instructions provided to configure, build from source, and create a Google API project. To see the sample in action, visit http://googledrive.github.io/web-quickeditor/#/edit/

The PayPal Python Sample Code by Gerry Lowry interacts with the capabilities of the PayPal REST API that include payments, sale transactions, refunds, authorizations, captures billing, invoicing, and notifications. In particular, this sample code complements a few videos featured on Paradigm Mentors, a website dedicated to train programmers with tutorials. More about Paradigm Mentors by Gerry Lowry at: https://paradigmmentors.com/about

Artificial Neural Networks is a concept that interconnects neurons with images. It is associated to image, speech, and handwriting functions of the brain. Created by Google developers Alexander Mordvintsev, Michael Tyka, and Christopher Olah, this repository provides IPython Notebook with sample code and a link to the Google Research article, "Inceptionism: Going Deeper into Neural Networks."

The official FullContact Open Business Card Reader iOS Sample Code offers guides to obtain an Api Key in the developer portal, set a webhook url, and update submodule dependencies. Requires iOS 7.0. More information about the API is associated to obtain business card data into an Apple application and the overall service is related to transfer contacts from business cards to digital formats. Visit https://www.fullcontact.com/developer/card-reader-api/

Author Dan Swain, developer with 7digital, published a guide to demonstrate how to create a music store with the 7digital Music API. Includes .NET and C# languages additional to Visual Studio Express Web Edition software. The tutorial shows videos and graphics to illustrate the step by step integration process. He also shares sample code with his favorite wedding songs at: https://github.com/7digital/SevenDigitalWalkthrough01

The TaxCloud JavaScript Sample Code for Stripe by TaxCloud demonstrates how to work with the API by using SOAP/XML or JSON protocols. Resources contain setup, code installation, locations section, products, customer, and purchase. The aim of this example is to integrate sales tax services in real time within one hour, considering users have previous development experience.

Its easy to use TaxCloud with Simplify Commerce to automatically calculate and collect sales tax for any street address in the United States. We are proud to announce the immediate availability of taxcloudSimplify.js, a new version of our TaxCloud javascript library that has been designed specifically for merchants using Simplify Commerce.

The code to the Objective-C style guide used by the New York Times is available in GitHub. It is a reference to the blog, "Objectively Stylish" by Matthew Bischoff, where the author mentions the aim to work in larger software projects, using a general iOS guide. Repository authored by chris@chrisdzombak.net
Objective-C style idea originally proposed by Brian Capps bcapps322@gmail.com

Presented as an extension, the Google Plus Hangouts sample code is a demonstration of a simple hangout app. Available as Gadget XML, Source Code, and Public App, the Google Plus Hangouts Apps aim to create new social experiences, create custom media effects, enable real-time collaboration, and increase social interaction. For more information about which Apps are associated to Hangouts, visit https://developers.google.com/+/hangouts/sample-apps

The Google Plus Hangouts Talking Heads code sample in JavaScript demonstrates how to change an avatar to a talking android of the user's preference. This code sample is available as repository in Google Code and as XML. Developers always have the option to Hangout to test this App with a Google account.

The Google Plus Hangouts Media App contains a code sample in JavaScript to consider in future integration projects. What the Media App does is to add and remove face-tracking overlays and play audio. Repository available in Google Code with monocle, mustache, and topHat as the main examples.

The Google Plus Hangouts Video Selector app demonstrates how to select a video either from the participant or the main video feed. To read code, visit the JavaScript repository available in Google Code.

The Google Plus Hangouts Face Movement Code Sample in JavaScript allows developers to study the possibilities of facial movement technology. One of the examples of this app is to customize facial recognition to add accessories with a company's logo. Repository available in Google Code.

Google Plus Hangouts Background Replacement Sample Code by Google. Demonstrates developers how to work in AJAX language to interact with the API functionalities of Hangouts. Particularly, Background Replacement has recently added API elements that can be found in this link: https://developers.google.com/+/hangouts/release-notes/hangouts#replacement

The Google Plus Hangouts OnAir Sample Code by Google demonstrates how to interact with moving participants in and out of the broadcast, characteristic of the Hangouts On Air. Using JavaScript language, developers have the opportunity to create projects to broadcast live from a YouTube account. More about OnAir in this link: http://www.google.com/+/learnmore/hangouts/onair.html

Learn how to create Android projects with Xamarin, the platform that helps to build mobile apps and develop software. In this guide, developers will review how to simplify code writing in C#, which is compatible with Android, iOS, Windows, and Mac. Along with requirements, topics include installation and configuration.

Official sample code to the WealthEngine API in Node.js language. Includes registration example in code and in form to personalize sales and marketing. Additional materials available on GitHub at https://github.com/WealthEngine/we-registration-form

This is a code sample in Ruby language for the SoundCloud API. What the API offers as integration features include music, audio, cloud, and streaming services. Author Rory Koehler recommends to consider Ruby version, system dependencies, configuration, database creation, database initialization, test suite, services, and deployment instructions.

The Spotify Echo Nest Roadtrip Mixtape project, plays the music of artists born where the roadtrip is taking place. For example, traveling from Boston to New York, users will listen to 'I don't want to miss a thing' by Boston based band, Aerosmith.

Sample code to facilitate interaction with Windows Azure Billing API, which aims to predict and manage billing information. To practice with this example, visit https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/billing-usage-rate-card-overview/

Withings is a company that offers devices to measure users' activity, weight, heart rate, sleep, and environment. The API allows to integrate calculations associated with physical and mental health into mobile applications. For a better understanding of how this works, an example in PHP language is available in Withings official site. The link provided in this site will automatically download the file. For more API info, visit http://oauth.withings.com/api
Category: Medical, Health, Internet of Things, Measurements

Description: The Alexa Web Information Service Ruby code sample is available to review how to interact with the API functionalities of web traffic and structure of the web. The Ruby code sample could provide an insight to develop with the AlexaApp Kit available at https://developer.amazon.com/public/solutions/devices/echo
Category: Search, Linked Data, URLs, Web Site Management

Description: Alexa Web Information Service code sample available in PHP language. API capabilities include URL information, historical web traffic, sites linking in, and browse category. This and all the code samples shared by AWIS can be useful to develop with the AlexaApp Kit available soon at https://developer.amazon.com/public/solutions/devices/echo
Category: Search, Linked Data, URLs, Web Site Management

Description:
This is a code sample in Java for the Alexa Web Information Service API, that offers URL information, historical web traffic, linked data, and category browsing. Community forum available at https://forums.aws.amazon.com/profile.jspa?userID=17092
Submitted by greg@alexa
Category: Search, Linked Data, URLs, Web Site Management

Description: The Alexa Web Information Service PERL code sample aims to demonstrate how to interact with the API capabilities such as web traffic and structure of the web. It was submitted by Greg@Alexa, who also opened a developers' forum in this link https://forums.aws.amazon.com/profile.jspa?userID=17092
Category: Search, Linked Data, URLs, Web Site Management

Description: Chargify offers subscription and recurring billing services. This sample code with PHP language and Zend Framework 1, was developed by Dan Bowen before the creation of a customer portal. Includes an app along with code to demonstrate the functionality for Chargify and Chargerly, both projects of Crucial Web Studio in Chicago, IL, USA.

Perfect Money allows to make payments and transfer money through the Internet. The code samples available in PERL, PHP, and Python contain similar information to interact with the API with the difference to work in a specific language of choice. Common topics include transfer funds to different accounts, get e-Vouchers, and verify payments.

Walk Score provides real estate options to live a walkable lifestyle, which increases residents' health, economy, and environment. The Walk Score AJAX API code sample demonstrates how to make an AJAX call using JQuery JavaScript library, how to call the Walk Score API, and how to return responses to the JavaScript client. For additional information, visit https://www.walkscore.com/how-it-works/

500px is an online community of photographers and photography enthusiasts who can showcase, buy, and sell art. Code examples might be useful to interact with the API capabilities before reading and writing data for new applications. Languages include PHP, Ruby, Java, Objective-C, and Python.

The CensusCity SDK allows to integrate Census data into local and national applications. Tutorials explain in more detail how to use the Census module to create data, how to create modules, and how to use multiple modules. Examples show BingMaps with GeoRequest, Farmers Market with its lookup tool, and Chicago Payroll Example with Socrata and SoQL.

With Google Gadgets, developers can enhance dynamic web content. The tutorial overviews Gadgets API extensions such as Calendar and G-mail which can be useful to run the gadgets in Blogger, Google Sites, and Google toolbar. Additional resources include how to create a user interface, how to work with remote content, and how to encode for internationalization.

Optical Character Recognition (OCR) allows to integrate recognition services into web services, software, and applications. The REST API offers code samples in .NET, Java, and PHP languages with the purpose to facilitate project implementation.

OCR Web Service integrates Optical Character Recognition to web services. It works with Android and iPhone in C#, Java, and PHP languages. The code samples for the SOAP API facilitate interactions with input and output parameters, methods, and values.

With the experimental app Fusion Tables, developers can create a map, create a business card layout, create summaries of data, share, and publish. Additional tutorials include more advanced techniques such as visualize data in Google Earth and use overlays in Google MapMaker.

The experiment Google Fusion Tables allows to visualize data online. This sample code guides users through the Visualization API, the Drive SDK, and the Google Maps JavaScript API. To study what other Fusion Tables developers have created, see https://developers.google.com/fusiontables/docs/tools

With the TomTom WEBFLEET.connect API, users can access data related to fleet vehicle management. In the process of integration, developers could benefit from a pair of code samples available in the official TomTom site. The first is the C# code sample and the second one is the Visual Basic code sample. The C# sample offers driver safety and efficiency resources, while the Visual Basic demonstrate how to retrieve an object list and send a text message using CSV and SOAP interfaces. For more information, visit http://business.tomtom.com/en_us/fleet-management/integration/resources/

The Yahoo Fantasy Sports PHP code sample aims to facilitate the interaction with the API data of fantasy football, baseball, basketball, and hockey. Includes game, league, team, and player information. The APIs are based on a RESTful model. Additional resources offer OAuth library use, OAuth flow without libraries, PUTs and POSTs, and public requests. More at https://developer.yahoo.com/fantasysports/guide/

FantasyData collects and distributes sports data in real time. The code samples available in the official site work with the NFL scores, stats, and news API. Languages include C#, Java, JavaScript, Objective-C, PHP, Python, and Ruby.
Languages: C#, Java, JavaScript, Objective-C, PHP, Python, Ruby

Description: Quizlet is an online learning tool created by Andrew Sutherland with the aim to make learning more exciting. The Quizlet PHP code sample demonstrates three steps authorization with the user, creating next an example API call. The objective of this code is to display the username and titles for the person who logs in. To gain a more clear idea, developers need to sign up for the 2.0 API.
Category: Education, Learning Management Systems, Testing, Tools

Description: Exact Online, an accounting software-as-a-service based in Netherlands, provides simple code samples to interact with the CSV API. Resources demonstrate how to import accounts, headers, and multiple lines in .NET and VB6 languages. Available lines of code to export name, address, and city for all accounts. Besides that these code lines could help to interact with the API, developers can move forward with the new API security standards to begin in August of 2015. More at https://developers.exactonline.com/Content/1506_RN_AppCenter_New_API_security_standards.htm

Gmail, the e-mail service owned by Google that provides options of storage, social interaction, and accounts also offers Gmail OAuth 2.0 code samples, useful for developers who work with Java, PHP, and Python languages. Each sample includes a link to start and download. Once developers find themselves on the other side of the links, they will see guides to configure, run the app, and explore the code on GitHub.

Yahoo BOSS offers customized solutions to improve search experiences. The Yahoo BOSS OAuth code samples aim to facilitate authorization for implementation practices, adjusting to C#, Java, Node.js, PERL, PHP, and Ruby languages. Some of the additional references include BOSS API specification, Yahoo BOSS API Arguments, and Universal Yahoo Sponsored Search Ads.
Languages: C#, Java, Node.js, PERL, PHP, Ruby

Description: With Yahoo BOSS, users can build projects to integrate customized searching engines. Code examples are available in C#, Java, Node.js, PERL, PHP, and Ruby languages. These samples are accompanied by other resources such as API keys, documentation, and Yahoo APIs, which use RESTful interface and display XML/JSON responses.
Languages: C#, Java, Node.js, PERL, PHP, Ruby

Description: The Google Cloud Print Python code samples act only as a reference to build applications with the Google Cloud Print API. Some of the topics display code to extract cookies, authenticate, register printer, and access printer jobs. In the site, developers can be aware that the last update of the code samples was done in 2011, reason why they should not implement the code into existing applications.

This tutorial demonstrates how to integrate Google Cloud Print into an Android application. It contains guides to submit print jobs and receive print jobs. Additional resources include PDF generation using Java libraries available at http://java-source.net/open-source/pdf-libraries

Beats Music API Tutorials available to learn how to search a catalog, play a track, manage playlists refresh an access token, stream contention, and access token user ID. An additional resource is the API playground, that displays OAuth 2.0 flow, client ID, and client secret of each one of the 13 APIs. APIs include activities, albums, artists, audio, highlights, genres, MyLibrary, me, playlists, recommendations, search, tracks, and users.

Blogger Raymond Camden offers examples of the Marvel Comics API in JavaScript. The samples are displayed in graphic form and code sample. One characteristic of Marvel Comics' developer portal is the interactive API tester. In this blog, users can see more detail about how to use the API in client-side and server-side applications with the aim to access data related to Marvel's comics, stories, and characters.

The E*TRADE tutorial to develop applications in Java explains how to authorize with OAuth and retrieve a list of accounts. With the aim to enhance learning, E*TRADE also offers REST API reference, SDK documentation, and code snippets. Developer resources available at https://developer.etrade.com/ctnt/dev-portal

The Etsy code sample by Jay Whitsitt aims to demonstrate the search with Etsy lists using the API. A section of files contain lines of code specifying Cocoa Pods with the aim to work with Apple devices. Some of the features that the Etsy API offers: listings, shops, and sales data. The API is built with RESTful interface and generates JSON responses.

This Google Webmaster Tools code sample exemplifies how to run an application in Java language. If the objective is to run the app, then developers first need to enable the API, install the library, and set up the sample. Once the goal is achieved, they can expand the sample into an application consulting the API reference at https://developers.google.com/webmaster-tools/v3/

Description: Wordpress (wordpress.org/) has been such a valuable tool when it comes to developing and designing beautiful client websites. While designing a custom Wordpress Dashboard for a client I realized that I would like to show-off to this particular client their Up and Downtime Statistics. What better way to accomplish that then to add it to the Dashboard. I foresee this Widget being much more powerful. The very first release will contain just basic code that you will add to your functions.php file. I based the original code around the example given by UptimeRobot (uptimerobot.com/) on their API page (uptimerobot.com/api) and added some Wordpress Functionality and Events. As it is right now, I can say that there is a lot that needs to be done. There is a lot that I dislike about the code at this point; I don't like inline styles, I don't like the simplicity of the code for security purposes. I encourage all to help build this widget up so that not only can we display these statistics to our clients but for multiple uses on your Wordpress Blogs and Websites. All constructive collaboration and criticism is welcome.
